s_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book brings together renowned scholars and new voices to challenge current practices in ELT materials design in order to work towards optimal learning conditions. It proposes ideas and principles to improve second language task design through novel resources such as drama, poetry, literature and online resources; and it maps out a number of unusual connections between theory and practice in the field of ELT materials development. The first section of the book discusses how innovative task-writing ideas can stretch materials beyond the current quality to make them more original and inspiring; the second part examines how different arts and technologies can drive innovation in coursebooks; the third section describes how teachers and learners can participate in materials writing and negotiate ways to personalize learning.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aLanguage teachersxTraining of. 0aSecond language acquisitionxStudy and teachingvTechnological innovations. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / English as a Second Language.2bisacsh  aCreativity.  aELT materials.  aELT.  acourse design.  acoursebooks.  amaterials design.  aonline resources.  atask design.  atextbook design.1 aBao, Dat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBao, Dat, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBegum, Hosne Ara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFloris, Flora D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaider, Md Zulfeqar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHullah, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiu, Ranran, econtribut